1 an urban area.
2 (4) In a county containing a consolidated local government, the mayor of the
3 consolidated local government, with the approval of the legislative body of the
4 consolidated local government, shall appoint the following seven (7) persons to
5 constitute the board of directors:
6 (a) Three (3) residents, one (1) from each of the three (3) commissioner's districts
7 in the county and no two (2) members shall reside within the same state
8 Senate district;
9 (b) One (1) resident of the county who shall also reside within and represent the
10 urban services district within the consolidated local government;
11 (c) One (1) resident of the county submitted by the organization representing the
12 largest amount of cities within the county which does not have statewide
13 membership;
14 (d) One (1) resident of the county who does not reside within a city or the urban
15 services district in the county; and
16 (e) One (1) resident of the county submitted by the association representing the
17 largest number of waste management entities operating within the county.
18 (5) A member of the board of directors may be removed from office pursuant to KRS
19 65.007.
20 (6) Except for the initial board appointed pursuant to this section, each director shall
21 serve a two (2) year term, and shall serve no more than three (3) consecutive terms.
22 The initial board appointed pursuant to this section shall consist of three (3)
23 directors appointed for one (1) year and four (4) directors appointed for two (2)
24 years.
25 (7) Notwithstanding KRS 65.008, a member serving on a board of directors in a
26 county containing a consolidated local government may serve until his or her
27 successor is appointed and qualified, not to exceed sixty (60) days after the
